\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Generating test package details**\\\\n\\\\nI need to generate a test package using convention underscores and include LoaderTest.java while utilizing AssertJ for assertions. It's important to check if the Java version is modern since the library might be old. The tests should include methods like `runDelegatedMainThroughLoader`, where I’ll create a loader instance and test the loading of classes and their methods. I’ve got to ensure I’m considering both access modifiers and class loading behavior correctly during the process.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Crafting loader test cases**\\\\n\\\\nI’m working on a few more test cases for my loader functionality. For instance, in the case where the parent loader is null, I can still assert that loading `java.lang.String` works correctly by directly finding the system class. I also want to explore scenarios where resource lookups occur, ensuring that if a class isn't found, it handles exceptions properly. Specifically, I’ll wrap calls in AssertJ to check for `ClassNotFoundException`. This should cover various resource lookup behaviors in my loader.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_1XcS9exngmx79SxslaCctNsd|fc_0edfe0cd0cfc85a20169f10b9eb9b081a0ae1f635721bd9faf\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/LoaderTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage javassist_javassist;\\n\\nimport javassist.Loader;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\\n\\npublic class LoaderTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void runsDelegatedMainClassWithArguments() throws Throwable {\\n        InvokedMain.reset();\\n        Loader loader = new Loader(LoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(), null);\\n        loader.delegateLoadingOf(InvokedMain.class.getName());\\n\\n        loader.run(InvokedMain.class.getName(), new String[] {\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"beta\\\"});\\n\\n        assertThat(InvokedMain.invocationCount()).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(InvokedMain.arguments()).containsExactly(\\\"alpha\\\", \\\"beta\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void delegatesPlatformClassLoadingToParentLoader() throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n        Loader loader = new Loader(LoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(), null);\\n\\n        Class<?> loaded = loader.loadClass(String.class.getName());\\n\\n        assertThat(loaded).isSameAs(String.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void delegatesPlatformClassLoadingToSystemLoaderWhenParentIsAbsent() throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n        Loader loader = new Loader(null, null);\\n\\n        Class<?> loaded = loader.loadClass(String.class.getName());\\n\\n        assertThat(loaded).isSameAs(String.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void attemptsOwnClassResourceLookupBeforeParentFallback() {\\n        Loader loader = new Loader(LoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(), null);\\n\\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> loader.loadClass(\\\"javassist_javassist.loader.MissingClass\\\"))\\n                .isInstanceOf(ClassNotFoundException.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class InvokedMain {\\n        private static int invocationCount;\\n        private static String[] arguments = new String[0];\\n\\n        public static void main(String[] args) {\\n            invocationCount++;\\n            arguments = args.clone();\\n        }\\n\\n        static void reset() {\\n            invocationCount = 0;\\n            arguments = new String[0];\\n        }\\n\\n        static int invocationCount() {\\n            return invocationCount;\\n        }\\n\\n        static String[] arguments() {\\n            return arguments.clone();\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 3044, \"output\": 1332, \"cacheRead\": 15872, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 20248, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777404819350, \"responseId\": \"resp_0edfe0cd0cfc85a20169f10b93cd1c81a09cccf00ade3b2675\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-34-30-743868Z.log:1566:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Generating test package details**\\n\\nI need to generate a test package using convention underscores and include LoaderTest.java while utilizing AssertJ for assertions. It's important to check if the Java version is modern since the library might be old. The tests should include methods like `runDelegatedMainThroughLoader`, where I’ll create a loader instance and test the loading of classes and their methods. I’ve got to ensure I’m considering both access modifiers and class loading behavior correctly during the process.\\n\\n**Crafting loader test cases**\\n\\nI’m working on a few more test cases for my loader functionality. For instance, in the case where the parent loader is null, I can still assert that loading `java.lang.String` works correctly by directly finding the system class. I also want to explore scenarios where resource lookups occur, ensuring that if a class isn't found, it handles exceptions properly. Specifically, I’ll wrap calls in AssertJ to check for `ClassNotFoundException`. This should cover various resource lookup behaviors in my loader.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0edfe0cd0cfc85a20169f10b95838c81a0bf0aaaa493f5c97d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":